<p>How do we interpret the standard deviation of X?</p>
<p>Xavier's production line produces an average of 1.80 defective parts per hour. The number of defective parts varies from hour to hour; typically (or, on average), it is about 1.21 away from 1.80.</p>
<p>Here is the formal definition:</p>
